        "body": "This pull request adds three JavaScript programs:\r\nFind Missing Number in a Sequence\r\nCheck Armstrong Number\r\nFind Longest Word in a String\r\n\r\nEach program focuses on solving a common algorithmic problem using simple logic and clean code structure.\r\n💡 Approach\r\n1️⃣ Find Missing Number in a Sequence\r\n\r\nCalculate the expected sum using the formula n * (n + 1) / 2.\r\nFind the actual sum of the array.\r\nThe difference between them gives the missing number.\r\n\r\nExample:\r\nInput: [1, 2, 4, 5] → Output: 3\r\n\r\n2️⃣ Check Armstrong Number\r\n\r\nConvert the number into digits.\r\nRaise each digit to the power of the total number of digits.\r\nIf the sum equals the original number, it’s an Armstrong number.\r\n\r\nExample:\r\nInput: 153 → Output: Armstrong number\r\n\r\n3️⃣ Find Longest Word in a String\r\nSplit the string into words using spaces.\r\nIterate and find the word with the maximum length.\r\n\r\nExample:\r\nInput: \"I love programming\" → Output: \"programming\"",
