        "body": "This pull request adds a new feature that counts the number of vowels (a, e, i, o, u) in a given string.\r\nThe function takes a string as input and returns the total count of vowels, ignoring case sensitivity.\r\n\r\nImplementation Details\r\n\r\nCreated a function count_vowels(string) that iterates through each character in the input.\r\nChecks whether the character is a vowel using a predefined set of vowels.\r\nReturns the count of vowels found in the string.\r\nHandles both uppercase and lowercase inputs.\r\n\r\nSubmitter checklist\r\n -Opened from a feature branch\r\n -PR title represents the changelog entry\r\n- Clearly described implementation and testing steps\r\n-Verified behavior with test cases\r\n\r\nfixes #2 ",
